            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-05T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-05T01:00:00-05:00" n="648" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d648">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50 Recovery/7–549: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Tsingtao</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hawthorne</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tsingtao</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-05T14:00:00+08:00">July 5, 1949—2 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 2:04 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>312. Director CUSA reports remaining ECA assets confiscated by Commies. These
                    include all cotton yarn due ECA from CTII<note n="49" xml:id="d648fn49">China
                        Textile Industries, Inc.</note> and Hwahsing cotton mill, small stock flour
                    and about 500 tons wheat, gunny bags and flour sacks and 14,000 Chinese silver
                    dollars CUSA had on hand for operating expenses.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 312, repeated AmEmbOff Canton.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hawthorne</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
